{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 9 provides a detailed illustration of the RetinaNet architecture, showcasing its innovative design.",
    "In addition to YOLO, SSD, and RetinaNet, other similar one-stage architectures are used in object detection.",
    "Popular examples include SqueezeDet (Wu et al., 2017), DSSD (Fu et al., 2017), DenseNet (Huang et al., 2017), and CornerNet (Law and Deng, 2018).",
    "SqueezeNet enhances accuracy in large object detections with its fire module backbone architecture but is limited on mobile platforms.",
    "Deconvolutional layer SSD (DSSD) is more efficient for dense and smaller objects in images, utilizing multi-scale predictions for higher accuracy results."
  ]
}